  "prompt": "What is the meaning of the name Ainsley?",
  "response": "The name Ainsley is of Old English origin, typically meaning \"one's own meadow\" or \"clearing.\" It is derived from the combination of the elements \"Anne\" or \"Annes\" and \"leah,\" which have been interpreted to represent a personal or ancestral clearing or meadow. The name can be used for both boys and girls, though it is more commonly given to girls in contemporary usage. The name evokes a sense of nature, tranquility, and personal space.",
